---
import type { CollectionEntry } from 'astro:content';
export interface Props { font: CollectionEntry<'fonts'>['data']; }
const { font } = Astro.props;
const fam = font.fontFamily;
---
<div class="iu" style={`--fam:${fam}`}>

  <!-- 01 — INTERACTIVE READER UI: real-scale long-form blog, adjustable size + reading mode + live progress -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">01</span><span class="label">Reader — long-form blog at real scale, fully interactive</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene">
      <div class="iu__device rdr" data-rdr>
        <div class="iu__chrome">
          <div class="iu__dots"><i></i><i></i><i></i></div>
          <span class="iu__addr">thecommonplace.org/the-comfort-of-a-screen-set-well</span>
        </div>

        <div class="rdr__bar">
          <span class="rdr__brand">The Commonplace</span>
          <div class="rdr__tools">
            <div class="rdr__size" role="group" aria-label="Text size">
              <button data-size="dn" aria-label="Smaller text">A</button>
              <span class="rdr__sizeval" data-sizeval>18&#8202;px</span>
              <button data-size="up" aria-label="Larger text" class="rdr__big">A</button>
            </div>
            <div class="rdr__modes" role="group" aria-label="Reading mode">
              <button data-mode="day" class="is-on" aria-pressed="true">Day</button>
              <button data-mode="sepia" aria-pressed="false">Sepia</button>
              <button data-mode="night" aria-pressed="false">Night</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rdr__progress" aria-hidden="true"><span class="rdr__progressfill" data-progress></span></div>

        <div class="rdr__scroll" data-scroll>
          <article class="rdr__article" data-article>
            <p class="rdr__kicker">Essay &middot; On Reading</p>
            <h3 class="rdr__title">The comfort of a screen set well</h3>
            <p class="rdr__byline">by Margaret Ashford &middot; <span class="rdr__fig">11</span> min read &middot; <span class="rdr__fig">June&#8201;2026</span></p>

            <p class="rdr__lede"><span class="rdr__drop">F</span>or most of its history the printed letter answered to ink and paper. A face was cut, a punch was struck, a matrix was justified, and a compositor set the line by hand. The whole apparatus existed to put marks on a sheet — and the letters that survived were the ones that printed cleanly, again and again, in that exact medium.</p>

            <p>The screen broke the contract. A backlit display flickers where paper holds still; it renders at a tenth of the resolution of fine printing; it throws light at the eye instead of reflecting it. A hairline serif that looked exquisite pressed into damp paper can simply vanish on a phone held at arm's length on a moving train.</p>

            <p>Libre Baskerville is what happens when a classic answers the new medium honestly. It keeps the bones of Baskerville's transitional roman — the upright stress, the bracketed serifs, the rational proportions that have signalled <em>the book</em> for two and a half centuries. But it quietly renegotiates every term that the screen would have broken.</p>

            <blockquote class="rdr__quote">A body face does its best work when you finish the paragraph without once having thought about the shapes that carried it there.</blockquote>

            <p>The x-height climbs, so more of every word lands in the band the eye actually scans. The counters open up, so an <em>e</em> or an <em>a</em> will not clog into a dark blot at sixteen pixels. The contrast eases back, so the thin strokes survive the glow instead of guttering out. None of it is showy. All of it is in service of the one thing a reading face is for: keeping you in the text.</p>

            <p>You can feel the result in the rhythm of a long passage. The line holds an even colour. The serifs lay a firm baseline that tugs the eye gently rightward and then returns it, cleanly, to the next line. There are no rivers, no flickering, no fatigue building behind the eyes after the third screen. This is typography as hospitality — the craft of making a reader feel, for a few thousand words, completely at home.</p>

            <p class="rdr__close">Drag the controls above and watch the column adapt: it was drawn to stay readable across every comfortable size and every light, because comfort, on a screen, is the entire point.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">Resize the type, switch Day / Sepia / Night, and scroll the column &mdash; the progress bar tracks you live. A real reading interface, the body face's true home.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 02 — LITERARY LONG-READ: magazine feature with drop cap, pull quotes, scroll reveals -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">02</span><span class="label">Magazine &mdash; a literary long-read spread</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene-mag">
      <div class="iu__poster mag">
        <header class="mag__head">
          <span class="mag__pub">Harborlight Review</span>
          <span class="mag__sec">Fiction &middot; Summer Reading</span>
        </header>
        <h3 class="mag__title">The Lighthouse Keeper&rsquo;s Last Winter</h3>
        <p class="mag__deck">A short story, in which a man who has tended a light for forty&#8202;years learns that the harbour means to switch it off.</p>
        <div class="mag__cols">
          <p class="mag__body"><span class="mag__drop">T</span>he letter came on the first calm day in November, which Aldous took, even then, as a discourtesy. The sea had been throwing itself at the rocks for a fortnight, and the one morning it lay flat enough for the supply boat to land, it brought him this. He read it twice at the foot of the stair, then once more at the lamp, as if the height might change the words.</p>
          <p class="mag__body">They were retiring the light. Automating it, the letter said, by the spring &mdash; a small electric thing that needed no keeper, no oil, no wick trimmed at two in the morning when the fog came down like a held breath. He was thanked for forty-one years of service. He was wished a comfortable retirement inland, near his sister, in a town he had visited exactly twice.</p>
          <blockquote class="mag__pull">He had given the light his eyes, his sleep, and the better part of his marriage. It had given him, in return, the one view in the world he could not imagine living without.</blockquote>
          <p class="mag__body">That night he climbed the stair as he always had, counting the hundred and twelve steps without thinking, and lit the lamp by hand. The beam swung out over the water, found the same black rocks it had found every night since he was a young man, and Aldous stood at the glass and watched it go, and did not feel, yet, anything he could have named.</p>
          <p class="mag__body">It was only later, with the kettle going and the wind picking up again outside, that the thought arrived plainly and would not leave: that come spring there would be a light here still, faithful and bright and entirely indifferent &mdash; and that nobody at all would be awake to keep it company.</p>
        </div>
        <footer class="mag__foot">
          <span class="mag__cont">continued on page <span class="mag__fig">48</span></span>
          <span class="mag__orn" aria-hidden="true">&#10086;</span>
        </footer>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">A magazine fiction spread &mdash; drop cap, a centred pull quote, true italics for emphasis and an even two-column reading colour.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 03 — EDITORIAL FEATURE OPENER: poster-scale title spread, italic/roman interplay, hover reveal -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">03</span><span class="label">Editorial &mdash; a feature opener</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene-open">
      <div class="iu__poster opener" data-opener>
        <span class="op__issue">The Commonplace &middot; Issue No. <span class="op__fig">07</span></span>
        <div class="op__center">
          <span class="op__over">a reading on</span>
          <h3 class="op__title">The Quiet<br/><em class="op__em">Letter</em></h3>
          <span class="op__rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <p class="op__stand">Why the typefaces we never notice are the ones that do the most work &mdash; and how a two&#8209;hundred&#8209;year&#8209;old serif learned to live behind glass.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="op__foot">
          <span class="op__by">Words by <em>Margaret&nbsp;Ashford</em></span>
          <span class="op__pp">pp. <span class="op__fig">24&ndash;33</span></span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">A feature title page &mdash; oversized roman against a swelling true italic, a hairline rule and oldstyle folios. Hover to let the rule draw across.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 04 — EMAIL NEWSLETTER: real device-scale artifact, distinct from the reading column -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">04</span><span class="label">Newsletter &mdash; an email issue at real scale</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene">
      <div class="iu__device news">
        <div class="iu__chrome">
          <div class="iu__dots"><i></i><i></i><i></i></div>
          <span class="iu__addr">inbox &middot; The Marginalia, Issue <span class="news__fig">112</span></span>
        </div>
        <div class="news__sheet">
          <header class="news__masthead">
            <span class="news__name">The Marginalia</span>
            <span class="news__tag">notes from the reading life &middot; weekly</span>
          </header>
          <div class="news__meta">
            <span>Issue <span class="news__fig">112</span></span>
            <span>Friday, <span class="news__fig">6</span> June <span class="news__fig">2026</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="news__lead">
            <p class="news__hello">Friends &mdash;</p>
            <p>This week I have been thinking about the difference between a letter that is <em>beautiful</em> and a letter that is <em>kind</em>. The first you admire. The second you forget entirely, which is the highest compliment a reading face can earn.</p>
          </div>
          <article class="news__story">
            <span class="news__num">01</span>
            <h4 class="news__h">Read this</h4>
            <p>An old essay on the etiquette of footnotes, newly reprinted &mdash; charming, exact, and set in a serif so comfortable I read it twice without meaning to.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="news__story">
            <span class="news__num">02</span>
            <h4 class="news__h">A line I kept</h4>
            <blockquote class="news__quote">&ldquo;A book is a machine to think with, but only if the type lets you forget it is there.&rdquo;</blockquote>
          </article>
          <article class="news__story">
            <span class="news__num">03</span>
            <h4 class="news__h">From the postbag</h4>
            <p>Three of you wrote in about reading on small screens at night. The short answer: larger line height, warmer light, and a face built for the medium. More next week.</p>
          </article>
          <footer class="news__foot">
            <p>Until Friday,<br/><em class="news__sign">Margaret</em></p>
            <p class="news__unsub">You are reading issue <span class="news__fig">112</span>. Reply any time &middot; <span class="news__link">unsubscribe</span></p>
          </footer>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">A weekly email issue &mdash; masthead, numbered notes, a kept quotation and a signed-off sign-off, all set at real inbox scale.</p>
  </figure>

</div>

<script>
  // ---- 01 reader: size, mode, live scroll progress ----
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-rdr]').forEach((rdr) => {
    const article = rdr.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-article]')!;
    const sizeval = rdr.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-sizeval]')!;
    const scroll = rdr.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-scroll]')!;
    const progress = rdr.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-progress]')!;

    let size = 18;
    const SIZES = [15, 16, 17, 18, 20, 22, 24];
    const applySize = () => {
      article.style.fontSize = size + 'px';
      sizeval.textContent = size + ' px';
    };

    rdr.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-size]').forEach((btn) => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const i = SIZES.indexOf(size);
        if (btn.dataset.size === 'up') size = SIZES[Math.min(i + 1, SIZES.length - 1)];
        else size = SIZES[Math.max(i - 1, 0)];
        applySize();
        updateProgress();
      });
    });

    const modes: Record<string, [string, string, string, string]> = {
      // [bg, fg, fg-2/3 muted, accent]
      day:   ['var(--bg)', 'var(--fg)', 'var(--fg-3)', 'var(--accent)'],
      sepia: ['#f4ecd8', '#3a2f22', '#8a7b60', '#9a5b2c'],
      night: ['#16181d', '#d7d3ca', '#8c8a85', '#c9b48a'],
    };
    const applyMode = (mode: string) => {
      const [bg, fg, mut, acc] = modes[mode];
      scroll.style.background = bg;
      article.style.setProperty('--rb', bg);
      article.style.setProperty('--rf', fg);
      article.style.setProperty('--rm', mut);
      article.style.setProperty('--ra', acc);
    };
    rdr.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-mode]').forEach((btn) => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        rdr.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-mode]').forEach((b) => {
          b.classList.remove('is-on'); b.setAttribute('aria-pressed', 'false');
        });
        btn.classList.add('is-on'); btn.setAttribute('aria-pressed', 'true');
        applyMode(btn.dataset.mode!);
      });
    });

    const updateProgress = () => {
      const max = scroll.scrollHeight - scroll.clientHeight;
      const pct = max > 0 ? (scroll.scrollTop / max) * 100 : 0;
      progress.style.width = Math.max(0, Math.min(100, pct)) + '%';
    };
    scroll.addEventListener('scroll', updateProgress, { passive: true });

    applySize();
    applyMode('day');
    updateProgress();
  });
</script>

<style>
  .iu__item { margin: 0; }
  .iu__hint { margin-top: var(--sp-2); color: var(--fg-3); }
  .iu__scene * { font-family: var(--fam); }

  /* shared figure helpers */
  .rdr__fig, .mag__fig, .op__fig, .news__fig { font-feature-settings: 'liga' 1, 'kern' 1; }

  /* ============================================================
     01 — READER UI (real px, interactive)
     ============================================================ */
  .rdr { font-size: 14px; }
  .rdr__bar {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding: 0.7rem 1.1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .rdr__brand {
    font-size: 19px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--fg); letter-spacing: 0.005em;
  }
  .rdr__tools { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.9rem; margin-left: auto; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .rdr__size {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
    padding-right: 0.9rem; border-right: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .rdr__size button {
    color: var(--fg-3); cursor: pointer; line-height: 1; padding: 0.1rem 0.25rem;
    font-weight: 700; transition: color 0.18s var(--ease);
  }
  .rdr__size button:hover { color: var(--fg); }
  .rdr__size button:first-child { font-size: 13px; }
  .rdr__big { font-size: 19px; }
  .rdr__sizeval {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--fg-3);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em; min-width: 4.2em; text-align: center;
  }
  .rdr__modes { display: flex; gap: 0.3rem; }
  .rdr__modes button {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--fg-3);
    padding: 0.32rem 0.62rem; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 100px;
    cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.18s var(--ease); white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .rdr__modes button:hover { color: var(--fg); border-color: var(--fg-3); }
  .rdr__modes button.is-on {
    color: var(--accent-contrast); background: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .rdr__progress { height: 2px; background: var(--line-soft); }
  .rdr__progressfill {
    display: block; height: 100%; width: 0%; background: var(--accent);
    transition: width 0.08s linear;
  }

  .rdr__scroll {
    height: 460px; overflow-y: auto; overscroll-behavior: contain;
    background: var(--bg); transition: background 0.3s var(--ease);
    scrollbar-width: thin;
  }
  .rdr__article {
    --rb: var(--bg); --rf: var(--fg); --rm: var(--fg-3); --ra: var(--accent);
    max-width: 64ch; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2.4rem clamp(1.4rem, 5cqi, 3.4rem) 3rem;
    font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.72; color: var(--rf);
    transition: color 0.3s var(--ease);
  }
  .rdr__kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ra); margin: 0;
  }
  .rdr__title {
    font-size: 1.85em; line-height: 1.12; font-weight: 700; color: var(--rf);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.6rem; letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  .rdr__byline { font-size: 0.82em; font-style: italic; color: var(--rm); margin: 0 0 1.6rem; }
  .rdr__lede { margin: 0 0 1em; }
  .rdr__article p { margin: 0 0 1em; }
  .rdr__article em { font-style: italic; }
  .rdr__drop {
    float: left; font-size: 3.1em; line-height: 0.7; font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.05em 0.12em 0 0; color: var(--ra);
  }
  .rdr__quote {
    font-size: 1.18em; line-height: 1.42; font-style: italic; color: var(--rf);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--ra); padding-left: 1rem; margin: 1.4em 0;
  }
  .rdr__close { color: var(--rm); }

  /* ============================================================
     02 — MAGAZINE LONG-READ (container-query print sizing)
     ============================================================ */
  .scene-mag > .iu__poster { position: relative; inset: auto; }
  .mag {
    background: var(--bg); color: var(--fg);
    padding: 6cqi 6cqi 5cqi; font-feature-settings: 'liga' 1, 'kern' 1;
  }
  .mag__head {
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); padding-bottom: 2.4cqi;
    font-size: 2cqi; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--fg-3);
  }
  .mag__pub { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
  .mag__title {
    font-size: 8cqi; line-height: 1.04; font-weight: 700; color: var(--fg);
    margin: 4cqi 0 0; letter-spacing: -0.01em; max-width: 16ch;
  }
  .mag__deck {
    font-size: 3cqi; line-height: 1.4; font-style: italic; color: var(--fg-2);
    margin: 2.4cqi 0 4cqi; max-width: 52ch;
  }
  .mag__cols {
    columns: 2; column-gap: 5cqi; column-rule: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    font-size: 2.3cqi; line-height: 1.62; color: var(--fg); text-align: justify; hyphens: auto;
  }
  .mag__body { margin: 0 0 0.9em; }
  .mag__body em { font-style: italic; }
  .mag__drop {
    float: left; font-size: 8.6cqi; line-height: 0.66; font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.05em 0.14em 0 0; color: var(--accent);
  }
  .mag__pull {
    break-inside: avoid; margin: 0.4em 0; padding: 1.4cqi 0;
    font-size: 3.1cqi; line-height: 1.32; font-style: italic; font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--accent); text-align: left; hyphens: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .mag__foot {
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline;
    margin-top: 4cqi; padding-top: 2.4cqi; border-top: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    font-size: 1.9cqi; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--fg-3);
  }
  .mag__orn { color: var(--accent); font-size: 3.4cqi; text-transform: none; }

  /* ============================================================
     03 — EDITORIAL FEATURE OPENER (poster-scale, cqi)
     ============================================================ */
  .scene-open { --card-ar: auto; }
  .scene-open > .iu__poster { position: relative; inset: auto; }
  .opener {
    background: var(--bg); color: var(--fg); min-height: 56cqi;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; padding: 6cqi 6cqi 5cqi;
    font-feature-settings: 'liga' 1, 'kern' 1;
  }
  .op__issue {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 2cqi; letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--fg-3);
  }
  .op__center {
    margin: auto 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; text-align: center;
  }
  .op__over {
    font-size: 2.6cqi; font-style: italic; color: var(--fg-3); letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1.6cqi;
  }
  .op__title {
    font-size: 17cqi; line-height: 0.92; font-weight: 700; color: var(--fg);
    margin: 0; letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .op__em {
    font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .op__rule {
    display: block; height: 1px; width: 0; max-width: 38cqi; background: var(--accent);
    margin: 4cqi auto; transition: width 0.9s var(--ease, ease-out);
  }
  .op__stand {
    font-size: 2.9cqi; line-height: 1.46; color: var(--fg-2); max-width: 46ch;
    margin: 0; font-style: italic;
  }
  .op__foot {
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline;
    margin-top: 5cqi; padding-top: 2.4cqi; border-top: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    font-size: 2.2cqi; color: var(--fg-3);
  }
  .op__foot em { font-style: italic; color: var(--fg-2); }
  .op__pp { font-family: var(--font-mono); letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  /* the hairline rule draws across on view; hover redraws it */
  .op__rule { width: 38cqi; }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
    .op__rule { width: 0; animation: op-draw 1.1s var(--ease, ease-out) 0.2s forwards; }
    .opener[data-opener]:hover .op__rule { animation: op-redraw 0.9s var(--ease, ease-out) forwards; }
  }
  @keyframes op-draw { to { width: 38cqi; } }
  @keyframes op-redraw { from { width: 0; } to { width: 38cqi; } }

  /* ============================================================
     04 — EMAIL NEWSLETTER (real px device scale)
     ============================================================ */
  .news { font-size: 14px; }
  .news__sheet {
    max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; background: var(--bg);
    padding: clamp(1.6rem, 5cqi, 2.8rem) clamp(1.4rem, 6cqi, 3rem) 2.4rem;
  }
  .news__masthead { text-align: center; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--fg); padding-bottom: 0.9rem; }
  .news__name { display: block; font-size: 34px; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; color: var(--fg); letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  .news__tag {
    display: block; margin-top: 0.5rem; font-size: 11px; font-style: italic;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: var(--fg-3);
  }
  .news__meta {
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--fg-3);
    padding: 0.7rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
  }
  .news__lead { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--fg); }
  .news__lead p { margin: 0 0 0.8em; }
  .news__hello { font-style: italic; color: var(--fg-2); }
  .news__lead em, .news__story em { font-style: italic; }
  .news__story {
    position: relative; padding: 1.4rem 0 1.2rem 2.6rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
  }
  .news__num {
    position: absolute; left: 0; top: 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--accent); letter-spacing: 0.04em;
